! Structural Selection

Expand and shrink selection by semantic units.

!! Features

* ''Progressive expansion'': Select larger semantic units
* ''Shrink back'': Return to previous selection
* ''Structure aware'': Recognizes words, markup, lines, sections

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

|!Key |!Action |
|Alt+Shift+Up |Expand selection |
|Alt+Shift+Down |Shrink selection |

!! Expansion Order

Selection expands through these levels:

# ''Word'': Current word under cursor
# ''Markup'': Enclosing wikitext markup (`[[...]]`, `''...''`, etc.)
# ''Line'': Full line(s)
# ''Section'': Heading section (until next same-level heading)
# ''Document'': Entire document

!! Example

Starting with cursor in middle of a word:

```
! My Heading

This is ''some [[important|link]]'' text.
              ^--- cursor here
```

Successive Alt+Shift+Up presses:

# `important` (word)
# `[[important|link]]` (link markup)
# `''some [[important|link]]''` (bold markup)
# `This is ''some [[important|link]]'' text.` (line)
# Entire section under "! My Heading"
# Entire document

Press Alt+Shift+Down to shrink back through each level.

!! Supported Markup

|!Markup |!Example |
|Links |`[[target]]`, `[[target|display]]` |
|Transclusion |`{{tiddler}}` |
|Macros |`<<macro>>` |
|Bold |`''text''` |
|Italic |`//text//` |
|Underline |`__text__` |
|Strikethrough |`~~text~~` |
|Superscript |`^^text^^` |
|Subscript |`,,text,,` |
|Code |`` `text` `` |

!! Configuration

|!Tiddler |!Values |!Default |
|`$:/config/Editor/EnableStructuralSelection` |`yes` / `no` |`yes` |

!! Widget Attribute

```
<$edit-text enableStructuralSelection="yes"/>
```

!! Notes

* Selection history is per-focus (cleared when editor loses focus)
* Always finds smallest enclosing unit first
* Section detection based on `!` headings